column5: SLOW , Dead , Suck's , Not that good Water temp still 63.5 On A bright note the Cat and Drum bite is great. This weather is just too nice But i'm afraid the longer it lasts the longer the fishing is not going to get any better , then Bam winter Sure shorting the season up here
but on the bright side, LOTW rocks.....big walleyes and lakers

X2. We fished the Winnipeg River and Traverse Bay Sept. 23 & 24 and caught a total of 3 walleye large enough to keep. Yes, we caught perch, pike, white bass, sauger, drum, bullheads but the greenback walleye are still absent. I agree with the comment on water temp being too high at 63F for good walleye fishing.
need some north winds to push the bait fish in
We just need some fisherman to show up. LOL
